  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Verbs of Hope (أفعال الرجاء)",
      "titleArabic": "أفعال الرجاء",
      "content": [
        "Verbs of hope (أفعال الرجاء) express hope or expectation that an action will occur.",
        "The most common is عَسَى (perhaps, may). Like كَادَ, they take a subject and predicate."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "عَسَى - perhaps, may, hopefully (عسى أن ينجح - may he succeed)",
        "حَرَى - is hoped (rarely used)",
        "اِخْلَوْلَقَ - is hoped (very rare)",
        "The predicate is typically أَنْ + subjunctive verb"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "عَسَى اللهُ أَنْ يَرْحَمَنَا", "english": "May Allah have mercy on us" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَى أَنْ يَأْتِيَ غَدًا", "english": "Perhaps he will come tomorrow" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَاهُ أَنْ يَنْجَحَ", "english": "May he succeed" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَيْتُمْ أَنْ تَفْهَمُوا", "english": "Perhaps you (pl.) will understand" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Conjugation of عسى",
      "titleArabic": "تصريف عسى",
      "content": [
        "عَسَى is a frozen verb with limited conjugation. It can take attached pronouns for the subject.",
        "The predicate always requires أَنْ before the subjunctive verb."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "عَسَى الطَّالِبُ - the student may...",
        "عَسَاهُ - he may...",
        "عَسَاكَ - you may...",
        "عَسَيْتُ - I may..."
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "عَسَاكَ أَنْ تَزُورَنَا", "english": "Perhaps you will visit us" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَاهَا أَنْ تَفْهَمَ", "english": "Perhaps she will understand" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَيْتُ أَنْ أَنْجَحَ", "english": "Perhaps I will succeed" },
        { "arabic": "عَسَاهُمْ أَنْ يَحْضُرُوا", "english": "Perhaps they will attend" }
      ]
    }
  ],
